The paper deals with online optimization problems, which are often studied in the areas of game theory (cs.GT), data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of convex optimization techniques also suggests a connection to convex optimization (cs.OH) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). However, since the paper focuses on resource allocation problems, we can rule out some sub-categories such as computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO).
